cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on wireless multimedia sensor networks and proposes a bandwidth balancing strategy for routing. This falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture.
2. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with video tracking and transmission in WMSNs, which is a multimedia application. 
3. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The CamShift based algorithm proposed in the paper is a computer vision technique used for object tracking. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper may also touch upon security issues related to video transmission in WMSNs. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a bandwidth balancing strategy which involves maintaining and predicting bandwidth capacity, which can be seen as a data structure and algorithmic problem.
